On pages like [Configuring Columns|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirasoftwarecloud/configuring-columns-764477997.html], you can see references to Design Guidelines:

{quote}
The single left-most column will always be blue, representing items in 'new' state (as per our [design guidelines|https://developer.atlassian.com/design/1.3/communicators/lozenges/]).
{quote}

The link currently points to {{developer.atlassian.com}} - but instead, it should point to {{https://atlassian.design/guidelines/product/components/lozenges}} or similar.

We should also check other links in the documentation to {{developer.atlassian.com}} to make sure there are no other broken links.

To reproduce:

# Add a custom field with a drop-down type
# Add a ticket with one of those options selected
# Post to 
{code:java}
/rest/globalconfig/1/customfieldoptions/{fieldid} 
{code}
to add an item (in doing so, you need to include current values/ids as well)
# See that the custom field on the ticket has been blanked, and with no record of the change in activity.
